# StreamLite — mandatory conventions

## Data fetching and API

- **Never** fetch data inside screen components (`src/screens/**`). Screens render UI only; they consume hooks and navigation.
- **Always** use custom hooks in `src/hooks/` for data fetching (e.g. `useHome`, `useSearch`, `useMovieDetail`).
- **Always** use the central API client from `src/api/client.ts` (or thin wrappers in `src/api/movies.ts`). **Never** import `axios` outside `src/api/client.ts`.
- For **parallel** independent requests (e.g. detail screen), use **`Promise.allSettled`** — not sequential `await` chains when sections must load independently.
- **Handle null / missing API fields** defensively: `poster_path`, `backdrop_path`, `runtime`, `vote_average`, empty arrays, etc. (placeholders, omit chips, section-level errors — per spec).

## Hook contract

Every data-fetching hook must return this shape (names and types as in project spec):

```typescript
{
  data: T | null;
  loading: boolean;
  error: string | null;
  refetch: () => void;
}
```

## Theme and layout

- **No hardcoded colors** — import tokens from `src/theme/colors.ts` only.
- **No hardcoded spacing** — use `src/theme/spacing.ts` (or derived spacing from tokens).
- **No 1px borders** for layout or section separation — use spacing and background colour shifts only (the “no-line” rule).

## TypeScript

- **Strict typing** — `no any`. Prefer interfaces from `src/api/types.ts` for API shapes.
- Navigation params must be typed in `src/navigation/types.ts` and used consistently.

## Folder structure

Follow `resources/project-spec.md` §5: `api/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `navigation/`, `screens/`, `store/`, `theme/`, `utils/` — do not invent parallel layouts.
